{
  "question_text": "<h3>Cut Off Trees for Golf Event</h3><p>Find minimum steps to cut all trees in increasing height order.</p>",
  "difficulty": "HARD",
  "marks": 10,
  "input_format": "2D grid.",
  "output_format": "Int.",
  "constraints": [
    "m, n <= 50"
  ],
  "explanation": "Sort all trees by height. Use BFS to find the shortest path between consecutive trees in the sorted list.",
  "answer": "def cutOffTree(forest):\n    trees = sorted([(forest[r][c], r, c) for r in range(len(forest)) for c in range(len(forest[0])) if forest[r][c] > 1])\n    def bfs(sr, sc, tr, tc):\n        q = collections.deque([(sr, sc, 0)]); v = {(sr, sc)}\n        while q:\n            r, c, d = q.popleft()\n            if r == tr and c == tc: return d\n            for nr, nc in [(r-1,c),(r+1,c),(r,c-1),(r,c+1)]:\n                if 0<=nr<len(forest) and 0<=nc<len(forest[0]) and forest[nr][nc] > 0 and (nr,nc) not in v:\n                    v.add((nr,nc)); q.append((nr,nc,d+1))\n        return -1\n    res = 0; sr = sc = 0\n    for h, tr, tc in trees:\n        d = bfs(sr, sc, tr, tc)\n        if d == -1: return -1\n        res += d; sr, sc = tr, tc\n    return res",
